3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the use of data-driven conversational systems, which involves the use of machine learning techniques such as sequence-to-sequence models. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The proposed approach involves the use of RNN-based methods, which are a type of neural network commonly used in natural language processing tasks.
